to the editor re on to los angeles still leaning left by jerry nachman op ed aug 13 if it is true that the majority of members of the news media are liberals it should not surprise anyone unlike average newspaper readers or television viewers your average reporter is likely to know a few things that most of us do n't like who runs the local soup kitchen or the safe house for battered women and how inadequate to their tasks each is or he knows the percentage of inmates in the local prison who are african american or he sits in a courtroom and watches a wealthy defendant get house arrest for doing the same thing that a penniless guy got 10 years for yesterday it may be that reporting on the human condition creates liberal reporters james mcgill st pete beach fla aug 15 2000

